==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Upbear
<hw>Up*bear"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To bear up; to
raise aloft; to support in an elevated situation; to sustain.</def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One short sigh of breath, <qex>upbore</qex>⟦br⟧
Even to the seat of God.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A monstrous wave <qex>upbore</qex>⟦br⟧
The chief, and dashed him on the craggy shore.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upbind</ent>⟦br⟧
